Image and File Information Speedlive may collect and upload users' image and file information for specific purposes within the app. This information may include, but is not limited to, images, documents, audio files, and videos uploaded or created by users. Collection and Use The image and file information collected by Speedlive is used solely for the purpose of providing the app's intended functionality and features. This may include processing and displaying user-generated content, facilitating sharing or collaboration features, or enhancing the user experience within the app. Storage and Security We take appropriate measures to ensure the security and confidentiality of the uploaded image and file information. This includes implementing industry-standard security protocols and encryption mechanisms to protect against unauthorized access, loss, or alteration of data. Sharing and Disclosure Speedlive does not share or disclose users' image and file information to third parties unless required by law or with the explicit consent of the user. However, it is important to note that user-generated content shared within the app may be visible to other users as per the app's functionalities. User Control Users have the ability to control their image and file information within the app. This may include the option to delete or remove uploaded content or adjust privacy settings associated with user-generated content. Please refer to the app's settings or user interface for specific controls and options available to you. Data Retention Speedlive retains users' image and file information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy or as required by law. Upon request or account deletion, we will make reasonable efforts to delete or anonymize the associated data, subject to any legal obligations or technical constraints.
